Heat oven to 325 degrees F. Combine shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar in bowl of electric mixer; beat at low speed until well blended. Add eggs; mix well. Add milk and vanilla extract, mixing well after each addition. Beat in pudding mix just until blended. Combine flour, 1/2 cup oats, coconut, baking soda and salt in medium bowl. Add to shortening mixture. Mix until blended. Stir in remaining 1 cup oats, regular and mini chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and pecans. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown around edges and slightly moist in center. Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet; transfer to cooling rack to cool completely.